Rating: 4
Gosh, was I nervous about trying this recipe after spending way too much money on these beautiful filet mignons and then reading someone's comment that the sauce had ruined an expensive cut of meat. However, unless I wanted to go back out to the store to get dried porcini mushrooms and tarragon to make the other recipe that sounded good, I didn't have much choice. I consoled myself knowing that I could taste the sauce before I drenched the filet in it. I say, "Drench the filet in it!" It's delicious! It is the perfect sauce for a rich meat. The color is not distracting or unappealing, by the way. One wise woman suggested shaking the filets in a ziploc with cracked pepper and sea salt: this is essential! Served with a baked ricotta and green salad.

